# Wikimyei Config Keys

`src/config/.config` section: `[WIKIMYEI]`

The Wikimyei section binds authored DSL files and grammars into the
graph-first protocol bundle. These paths are part of deterministic protocol
construction; when a component's semantic contract changes, update both its DSL
and BNF path entries.

## Observer Belief

- `wikimyei_observer_belief_dsl_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for `wikimyei.observer.belief.dsl`.
- `wikimyei_observer_belief_dsl_path`
  - Deterministic observer contract that converts Channel MDN NodeLift
    potential distributions into NodeLift-aware allocation belief semantics.
  - V1 requires feature semantics from the Ujcamei kline registry/dock
    coordinate space, numeraire-relative NodeLift projection,
    arithmetic-return scenarios, and an accounting numeraire supplied as a
    graph node by `BasePolicy`.
  - The DSL must keep `PROJECTION_VALIDATION_REQUIRED = true` and
    `LIVE_CAPITAL_ALLOWED = false` until projected NodeLift returns have an
    empirical validation artifact.

## Spot Distributional Utility Policy

- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_spot_distributional_utility_dsl_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for `wikimyei.policy.portfolio.spot_distributional_utility.dsl`.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_spot_distributional_utility_dsl_path`
  - Deterministic portfolio policy contract for the first allocation method.
  - V1 consumes only post-projection `AllocationBelief`, is long-only and
    spot-only, uses projected-gradient search over unified graph-node target
    weights, and requires the accounting numeraire to be included in that
    target-node universe.
  - The policy DSL mirrors the observer safety flags:
    `PROJECTION_VALIDATION_REQUIRED = true` and `LIVE_CAPITAL_ALLOWED = false`.

## Graph Node Allocation Policy

- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_dsl_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for `wikimyei.policy.portfolio.graph_node_allocation.dsl`.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_dsl_path`
  - Contract-only trainable policy surface for future graph-node allocation policies.
  - V1 consumes `kikijyeba.environment.policy_input.v1` and emits
    `kikijyeba.environment.action.target_node_weights.v1` through
    `target_node_weights_simplex.v1`.
  - `ACTION_DISTRIBUTION = masked_dirichlet_simplex.v1` is the default
    pre-PPO stochastic action law. `masked_logistic_normal_simplex.v1` is
    accepted as a contract candidate, but is not the default.
  - The accounting numeraire remains an ordinary graph node inside the same
    target-node weight vector; there is no separate cash output.
  - `RAW_MDN_INPUT_ALLOWED = false`, `PPO_IMPLEMENTED = true`, and
    `LIVE_CAPITAL_ALLOWED = false` are required. PPO V0 is Runtime-owned and
    replay/paper-only.
  - Runtime `ppo_policy_artifact_contract.v1` gates executable PPO-shaped
    policy facts. It requires actor/critic checkpoint and architecture
    digests, optimizer state, PPO config, rollout collection, PPO update
    report, validation rollout report, GAE identity, and PPO hyperparameters.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_net_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for `wikimyei.policy.portfolio.graph_node_allocation.net`.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_net_path`
  - Architecture identity for the bounded PPO V0 graph-node allocation policy.
    V1 binds the feature manifest, node/global/risk encoder shape,
    mask-aware pooling, `node_weight_logits` policy head, `state_value` critic
    head, Dirichlet default distribution config, logistic-normal candidate
    config, and the action adapter/distribution. Raw timestamp and anchor
    identity stay outside the actor-visible global feature tensor.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_features_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for
    `wikimyei.policy.portfolio.graph_node_allocation.features.dsl`.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_features_path`
  - Actor-feature manifest for the graph-node allocation policy. It freezes
    the 28 node features, 6 global features, and 10 compact cross-node risk
    features used by `kikijyeba.environment.policy_input.v1`, while declaring
    raw MDN tensors and the full scenario bank forbidden for V1.

`src/config/.config` section: `[JKIMYEI]`

- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_jkimyei_bnf_path`
  - Grammar for the graph-node allocation PPO V0 `.jkimyei`.
- `wikimyei_policy_portfolio_graph_node_allocation_jkimyei_path`
  - Bounded PPO V0 policy-training profile. It requires
    `TASK = policy_graph_node_allocation_ppo_v0`, `OPTIMIZER = ppo_clip`,
    `TRAINING_SCHEDULE_MODE = causal_walk_forward_training.v1`, and
    `PPO_EXECUTION_ALLOWED = true`; live capital remains forbidden by the
    policy DSL and Runtime authority.

These observer and policy assemblies are included in the graph-first
`wikimyei_registry` and dock-binding report. Lattice can audit their identity
and dock compatibility, but execution authority remains outside Lattice.
